article.headline: Sinani's 24 lead Campbell past Navy 86-66
article.description: — Jasin Sinani had 24 points in Campbell's 86-66 victory over Navy on Sunday.
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- — Jasin Sinani had 24 points in Campbell's 86-66 victory over Navy on Sunday. Sinani shot 6 for 11 (2 for 5 from 3-point range) and 10 of 11 from the free-throw line for the Fighting Camels (3-2). Terren Frank shot 8 for 13, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc to add 17 points. Nolan Dorsey shot 4 for 5, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. Aidan Kehoe finished with 14 points and nine rebounds for the Midshipmen (1-3). Navy also got 14 points and five assists from Austin Benigni. Lysander Rehnstrom had 11 points. Campbell took the lead with 4:31 left in the first half and never looked back. The score was 38-33 at halftime, with Sinani racking up 15 points. Campbell extended its lead to 82-59 during the second half, fueled by a 12-3 scoring run. Dorsey scored a team-high 10 points in the second half as his team closed out the win. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
